Cara S
Columbia, MO13 contributions
DO NOT BOOK WITH APT Travel.
Mar 2015 ‚Ä¢ Friends
First, Halong Bay is beautiful. The rocks, landscape and scenery is simply stunning. The bay itself is quite trashy and dirty. Luckily it was too cold to swim, because I would not have wanted to get in the water give its dirty state.
We booked a 3 day/2 night cruise for $130. This was quite high for Vietnam, so we were expecting something a lot better than what we actually got. The boat itself was a bit sketchy but the rooms were nice. the first day went okay with great scenery, and a visit to the caves and kayaking. It ended with a forced "dance party" with a few hours of free beer, where one of the guides made up a drinking game that involved making out with him - which was beyond sketchy. The next morning we were immediately told to pack our things, but not told we had an event at 9am, meaning the boat nearly left part of my party behind because no times were discussed. After coming back from the oyster farm, we basically sat around until another boat came that was supposed to transport us to the "island" we were staying for the night.
The boat arrived, we picked up some new people, lost a few of the people on our boat, and headed to a national park. Before we arrived we were told bikes for the park were $5 USD, which we paid prior to leaving the boat, but I did not see our guide - Frank - pay anyone, leading the entire boat to believe he pocketed the money. Before we left the boat Frank told us to take our valuables with us, which most people did. We then spent about two hours in the park, and when we returned all of our bags had been searched through.
While we were biking the park, the crew went through all of our bags and STOLE MONEY. The bags looked like they had been ransacked and money had been removed from places people had "stashed" some of their money (so they weren't carrying it all on themselves). Frank then said that it didn't happen and that we must have lost the money.
We we finally arrived at the island, after the bag-searching fight, we were then taken to our "bungalows" which happened to be "full" therefore we were told to stay in a 30-person dorm. This was exactly the opposite of what we had been told, since we were expecting a private room. After nearly two hours of fighting with Frank, we finally got some of the money back, and moved to a hotel with single rooms. The hotel was bad, but better than the dorm for sure.
After this event, our tour guide Frank, became extremely hostile and yelled at us nearly every time we interacted. It was a quick 180 and an unwelcome change in his personality, especially since we were forced to spend time with him on the boat. I wish he could have been consistently nice and supportive throughout the event rather than getting hostile for no apparent reason (even prior to the money-stealing incident).
Overall, this company is no good. They are not the "booking" agents, but rather the group that implements the bookings, meaning they have basically no idea what you were "promised" when you booked. I do recommend seeing Halong since it is very beautiful and the scenery is unparalleled, but I do not recommend this company, or taking part in the two night program. If you can, avoid the cave and ask to head to the national park instead.
My only recommendation is that you be careful when booking, to make sure you are working with a legitimate company who can act on what they promised when you booked and paid.
